USA: Trains crash in W. Virginia, two presumed dead.Trains crash in W. Virginia, two presumed dead.Two railroad workers were presumed dead after two freight trains carrying hazardous chemicals collided head-on Tuesday in Smithfield, West Virginia, emergency officials said.Carla Morris of the Wetzel County Office of Emergency Services said the workers were presumed killed but could not identify them.Hazardous materials crews were at the scene cleaning a spill of polyvinyl chloride pellets, said Karen Simsen, a state police spokeswoman.The trains were part of a fleet owned by CSX Transportation Inc of Jacksonville, Florida, a subsidiary of CSX Corp of Richmond, Virginia.